#: ./doc/security-guide/ch047_data-encryption.xml:26(para)
msgid "The ability to encrypt objects in Object Storage is presently limited to disk-level encryption per node. However, there does exist third-party extensions and modules for per-object encryption. These modules have been proposed upstream, but have not per this writing been formally accepted. Below are some pointers:"
