#: ./doc/security-guide/ch052_devices.xml:334(para)
msgid "The <literal>svirt_image_t</literal> label uniquely identifies image files on disk, allowing for the SELinux policy to restrict access. When a KVM-based Compute image is powered on, sVirt appends a random numerical identifier to the image. sVirt is technically capable of assigning numerical identifiers to 524,288 virtual machines per hypervisor node, however OpenStack deployments are highly unlikely to encounter this limitation."
