#: ./doc/security-guide/ch042_database-overview.xml:9(para)
msgid "Each of the core OpenStack services (Compute, Identity, Networking, Block Storage) store state and configuration information in databases. In this chapter, we discuss how databases are used currently in OpenStack. We also explore security concerns, and the security ramifications of database backend choices."
