#: ./doc/security-guide/ch042_database-overview.xml:111(para)
msgid "Finally, it should be noted that as of the Grizzly release, gaps exist where <systemitem class=\"service\">nova-conductor</systemitem> is not used throughout OpenStack Compute. Depending on one's configuration, the use of <systemitem class=\"service\">nova-conductor</systemitem> may not allow deployers to avoid the necessity of providing database GRANTs to individual compute host systems."
